The paper deals with the semantics and implementation of aggregates in Answer Set Programming (ASP), which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (AI) that focuses on declarative problem solving. The paper also involves logical reasoning and complexity analysis, which are topics in Logic (LO) and Programming Languages (PL). Additionally, the paper discusses compilation techniques for implementing the new semantics, which is related to Databases (DB) and Data Structures (DS). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DB, and cs.DS.
